comment_data.body:
This looks to be an error inside your Python headers which suggests to me that it isn't a Cython problem but is to do with your installation of Python. Simply including Python.h should not give this kind of errors.

I'll close this for now, but if you can edit in enough detail to give a minimal example that we can try to reproduce then we might be able to give better confirmation about whether it's a Cython bug.

Actually, looking at it in more detail there's two things that show:
* warnings for `warning: 'struct timeval' declared inside parameter list will not be visible outside of this definition or declaration` (which may or may not be valid, but come from the Python headers and not Cython)
* Linking errors. You need to link your program/module against libpython. The [cython users](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/cython-users) mailing list may be able to help you. The bug tracker isn't a support forum though

title: [BUG] main.c generated by cython isn't running
